  <data name="UnitShieldAvgLabel.ToolTip" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Shield value divided by the mean damage modifier across key damage types to the unit's armor type
Combat power calulations use the closely related shield*average damage absorption or shield*(1 - mean modifier)</value>
  </data>
  <data name="UnitHpAvgLabel.ToolTip" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Health value divided by the mean damage modifier across key damage types to the unit's armor type
Combat power calulations use the closely related hp*average damage absorption or hp*(1 - mean modifier)</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TargetAccuracyLabel.ToolTip" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>DPS lowered by the inaccuracy of each weapon toward the selected category. Also includes range and armor/shield type modifers
The collision system in EaW means "missed" shots can still hit the target, especially for larger units, and "hits" can miss accelerating/turning targets.
The end value is only an approximation of how many of the shots fired should land.</value>
  </data>
